Let me tell you a story. Are you ready? Make sure your belt buckles are tight, and your zipper is down. You just might piss yourself.\
A student subscribes to the model of the University. The University says that if you study hard, get a good GPA, pursue extracurriculars, then you will succeed in getting a nice job. The graduate subscribes to the model of the job - if you work hard, you will earn money, more vacation, and a promotion. The employee subscribes to the model of retirement, once you earn enough money, work hard enough, you can relax. And so he relaxes. But what model is he meant to subscribe to now? Who is to tell him how to relax? And we wonder why old people have so much free time.\
That was more broad, but it doesn't have to be, let's zoom in a bit. There is a failing marriage, a man and a woman. The man is a deadbeat husband, but in the past, he was good. The wife, though having lost her attraction to him, is sticking around. She subscribes to the model that if she waits long enough, then he is sure to treat her well again. If he doesn't change to treat her better, it's on him, not her. And even if it all goes bad, it's not her fault that she didn't leave before, 
